replies.body:
Before;
Supports would peel you buy landing crucial abilities such as Tornadoes at a CRUCIAL moment (such as cancelling a dash that would have been re-settable had it landed) 
Now;
Janna slaps a shield on her ADC and watches as Ardent Censor and the all the ability power she's gained from passive gold does the work. Does the enemy team play well and pose a threat? NP, just press R and invalidate all of the damage done with your heal, which is now healing for ludicrous amounts since you're getting your items faster and thus scaling faster.

Basically, Supports are straight out stat checking people. Tank Supports are SUPER tanky, Damage supports (such as Bard) are doing tons of burst damage, while peel supports such as Lulu/Janna aren't keeping their adcs alive by correctly timing their abilities and what not, but rather purely by buffing their ADCs to ungodly levels.
